  ('WS4', 'De La Riva Sweep (Back Trip Sweep)', 'white', 'Sweeps', 65.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15.0, NULL, NULL, 'GREEN if used value >= 15 after age/injury modifiers; otherwise YELLOW or RED per TechniqueEligibility formulas. RISK: <60° hip ER OR <110° hip flex = Very High Risk (knee torque risk)'),
  ('BC1', 'Ashi Garami (Single Leg X Control)', 'blue', 'Controls', 60.0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15.0, NULL, NULL, 'GREEN if used value >= 15 (BOTH side) after age/injury modifiers; otherwise YELLOW or RED per TechniqueEligibility formulas. RISK: Hip ER <55 → compensatory knee torsion on controlling legs; precursor to ankle lock & knee bar — dynamic sub load on top of high ROM demands; exposes both athletes to reciprocal leg attacks. Confidence: MEDIUM'),
